Module Mal4J

Package com.kttdevelopment.mal4j

Contains core classes for accessing MyAnimeList.
  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    AuthResponseHandler
    The response handler determines what the webpage will look like after the user authenticates with MyAnimeList.
    MyAnimeListAuthenticationService
    Represents the HTTP requests for authentication.
    MyAnimeListService
    Represents the HTTP requests for MyAnimeList
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    AccessToken
    Represents an OAuth2 authentication body.
    APICall
    Represents an API call.
    APIStruct
    Annotations used to structure API calls.
    APIStruct.Response<T>
    Represents HTTP response.
    Fields
    This fields class holds all possible fields for a request.
    Fields.Anime
    All possible fields for an Anime.
    Fields.Anime.ListStatus
    All possible fields for an Anime list status.
    Fields.Anime.MyListStatus
    All possible fields for an Anime list status.
    Fields.Common
    Fields shared by Fields.Anime and Fields.Manga.
    Fields.Common.ListStatus
    Fields shared by Fields.Anime.ListStatus and Fields.Manga.ListStatus.
    Fields.Manga
    All possible fields for a Manga.
    Fields.Manga.Authors
    All possible fields for an Author.
    Fields.Manga.ListStatus
    All possible fields for a Manga list status.
    Fields.Manga.MyListStatus
    All possible fields for a Manga list status.
    Fields.Manga.Serialization
    All possible fields for serialization.
    Fields.User
    All possible fields for a User.
    Json
    A massively simplified json parsing class.
    Json.JsonObject
    Represents map as a json object.
    MyAnimeList
    The MyAnimeList API interface, used to execute requests with the API from Java.
    MyAnimeListAPIResponseMapping
    Represents the MyAnimeList API response as an object.
    MyAnimeListAPIResponseMapping.Anime  
    MyAnimeListAPIResponseMapping.Common  
    MyAnimeListAPIResponseMapping.Forum  
    MyAnimeListAPIResponseMapping.Manga  
    MyAnimeListAPIResponseMapping.User  
    MyAnimeListAuthenticator
    Documentation: https://myanimelist.net/apiconfig/references/authorization
    Authenticator is used to retrieve OAuth2 tokens given a client id and client secret.
    MyAnimeListAuthenticator.LocalServerBuilder
    Creates a MyAnimeList Authenticator by deploying a local server to authenticate the user.
    MyAnimeListImpl
    Implements the MyAnimeList interface with the MyAnimeListService.
    PaginatedIterator<T>
    Represents a paged response.
  • Exception Summary 
    Exception Description
    HttpException
    Thrown if the server does not return a 200 OK response.
    Json.JsonSyntaxException
    Thrown then the json is malformed
    UnauthorizedAccessException
    Thrown if the state parameter was illegally modified.
